(230, 'ETHERNET TECHNOLOGY TRAINING', '', 'INGENIERIA', 'TIC', 'GENERICO', '02_00GN02_04', 'Basic knowledge in IP and Ethernet$ Knowledge with digital Radio / Relay equipment$ Experience in the use of Test and Measurement Instruments for digital equipment$ Each person must bring a PC for the simulation practices.', 'Describe the data network’s operation$Select the specifications required to achieve certain network components.  $OSI Model.  $Use the OSI and TCP / IP models and their associated protocols to explain how data flows in a network.$Describe common networked applications including web applications.$Describe the purpose and basic operation of the OSI and TCP / IP protocols models.$Describe the impact of applications (VoIP, Video over IP) on a network.  $Interpret network diagrams.  $Determine the path between two hosts through the network.  $Describe the components required for network communications and internet  \r\n$Identify and correct common network problems (layers 1,2,3, 7)  $Differentiate the characteristics and operation between LAN / WAN$Implement small networks with Switching$Ethernet Frame Structure  \r\n$Explain the technology and media access control method for Ethernet technologies.  $Explain network segmentation and basic traffic management concepts.  $Explain the operation of switches and basic switching concepts.  $Perform, save and verify initial configuration tasks on a switch including remote access management.  $Verify network status and operation of the switches using basic utilities (ping, traceroute, telnet, SSH, ARP, ipconfig) including show and debug commands.  $Implement and verify basic security for a switch (port security, deactivate ports).  $Protocol 802.1P (Priority Tagging / mapping), 802.1Q (VLAN Tagging)  \r\n$Identify and resolve common problems in network switches from the path, configuration, auto-negotiation and Hardware failures.  $Connectivity Fault Management CFM 801ag$Implement a scheme of the IP routing and IP services for small networks requirements $Create and apply an addressing scheme to a network.  $Assign and verify valid IP addressing for hosts, servers and network devices in a LAN.  $Explain the basic use and operation of NAT in a small network connecting to an ISP.  $Describe and verify the DNS operation.  $Describe the operation and benefits of using private and public IP addressing.  $Enable NAT for small networks with a single ISP and connection using SDM verifying the operation using CLI and Ping.  $Configure, verify and troubleshoot the DHCP and DNS operation on a router (using CLI / SDM).  $Implement static and dynamic addressing services for hosts in a LAN environment.  $Identify and fix IP addressing issues  $802.3 ad Protocol, Link Aggregation$Implement small networks with Routing$Describe the operation of routers (router boot process, POST, router components)  $Select the appropriate media, cables, ports, and connectors to connect routers to other network devices and hosts.  $Configure, verify, and troubleshoot RIPv2  $Access and use the router CLI to set basic parameters.  $Connect, configure and verify the interfaces operation and status.  $Verify device configuration and network connectivity using (ping, traceroute, telnet, SSH and other utilities).  $Check the performance and verify configurations of static routes or default route given specific conditions.  $Managing configuration files in IOS (save, edit, upgrade, restore).  $Manage IOS.  \r\n$Implement password and physical security.  $Verify network status and router operation using basic utilities (ping, traceroute, Telnet, SSH, ARP, ipconfig) including show and debug commands.  $Span Tree Protocol\r\n$Identify security issues in a network and describe general methods to mitigate those problems$Explain the current increase in security problems and the necessities to implement appropriate security policies to mitigate attacks.  $Explain general methods to mitigate the most common attacks to the net